Conclusion and Recommendations¶










Conclusion¶










Analyzed the data of nearly 180 customers of the treadmill product(s) of a retail store called Cardio Good Fitness. The main feature of interest here is the Product. From the Analysis, we observe that


    

  1. Most of the customers fall in the age group 24-27 years. 
    2. 

  2. most of the customers have 14- 16 years of experience. 
    3. 

  3. Most of the customers want to use the threadmill for 3-4times/week.
    4. 

  4. The Income of majority of the customers falls between (40000-60000)
    5. 

  5. Customers busying the equipment are mostly Men.
    6. 












It is also observed that most of the customers prefer to use TM798 followed by TM498 and TM195.


    

  1. Customers with higher income, those who prefer to run more miles and whose fitness rating is higher prefer to use TM798. 
    2. 

  2. Customers with lower income, average usage and less years of education prefer TM498. 
    3. 

  3. Customers with less fitness rating, lesser miles and lower Income prfer TM195. 
    4. 












Recommendations¶










    

  1. Since, TM798 is preferred by higher income customer. Increasing the price of this product by introducing new features can result in higher sales.
    2. 

  2. Since, TM195 is preferred by customers whose usage is low and income being low, this can be used as a alternative. Also, since, many customers fall in the average income category, 
 this product can be maintained at low budget for higher sales. 
    3. 

  3. Customers with Average income, average education years and average usage prefer TM498. This price of this product can be in between 
TM798 and TM195 with better features compared to TM195. 
    4.
